    "recap_headline": "Ohio State Buckeyes | Ohio State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "COLUMBUS, Ohio\n\u2013 Sophomore right-handed pitcher\nGavin Kuzniewski\nthrew his first career complete game shutout as the Ohio State baseball team (8-12) down Butler (5-17), 11-0, in seven innings on Friday night.\nGame Recap\nIn the bottom of the first inning,\nNoah Furcht\nscored the first run of the game on a pick-off play to give the Buckeyes an early 1-0 lead.\nDane Harvey\nled off the bottom of the second inning with a double to right field. Harvey and\nSteven Cavaco\nscored on a two-run double from\nMiles Vandenheuvel\ndown the left field line. On the following pitch,\nCJ Reid\nripped a single to center field to send Vandenheuvel home and give the Buckeyes a 4-0 lead.\nIn the bottom of the fourth inning with two outs, Reid drew a walk and\nAlex Bemis\nreached base on a Butler error to put two runners on for the Buckeyes.\nHenry Kaczmar\nsingled to center field to score Reid. Furcht was up next at the dish, and he crushed a two-RBI triple, which brought home Bemis and Kaczmar. Furcht then scored off a Butler error to extend the Buckeye lead, 8-0.\nIn the bottom of the fifth inning,\nMaddix Simpson\nand Cavaco drew back-to-back walks, and then executed a successful double steal. Vandenheuvel walked to load the bases, and Reid was hit by a pitch to send Simspn home and give the Buckeyes a 9-0 lead over the Bulldogs.\nMason Eckelman\nwas hit by a pitch to lead off the home half of the sixth, followed by a single from Harvey. A sacrifice bunt from Simpson moved both runners into scoring position. An RBI groundout from Cavaco scored Eckelman and Harvey scored on a wild pitch to give the Buckeyes a double-digit lead, 11-0.\nWith one out and one runner on in the top of the seventh, the Buckeyes turned a 1-6-3 double play to ice the 11-0 run-rule, shutout victory.\nBuckeyes by the Numbers\nKuzniewski (1-1) threw the first complete game of his career.\u00a0He\u00a0had five strikeouts\u00a0and only gave up five hits in 7.0 innings pitched.\nFurcht led the Buckeyes at the plate with three hits.\nFurcht,\u00a0Reid\u00a0and\u00a0Vandenheuvel\u00a0shared the team lead in RBIs with two each.\nEvery Buckeye in the lineup scored at least one run, with\u00a0Furcht\u00a0and Harvey each scoring two.\nUp Next\nThe Buckeyes continue their series with Butler Saturday, May 21-Sunday, May 22. Saturday is Senior Day at Bill Davis Stadium, with the Senior Day ceremony set to begin at 2:25 p.m. Sunday is Zach Farmer Day.\n#GoBucks",
